=head1 DESCRIPTION

A batch job identifier in which the batch jobs to run are identified by
an Amazon S3 location.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Bucket => Str

The Amazon S3 bucket that contains the batch job definitions.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Identifier => L<Paws::M2::JobIdentifier>

Identifies the batch job definition. This identifier can also point to
any batch job definition that already exists in the application or to
one of the batch job definitions within the directory that is specified
in C<keyPrefix>.


=head2 KeyPrefix => Str

The key prefix that specifies the path to the folder in the S3 bucket
that has the batch job definitions.



